It just occurred to me why Conor wants this fight at 170. He doesn't want the "best Cerrone"; he just wants to make sure he gets CERRONE. He's afraid of anyone who might step in. He's willing to fight the Tonys and Khabibs, but to start 2020, he needs this win or there is no 2020 for Conor. If he loses this fight, he's taking a long break.

Side note, the only reason Conor doesn't want a war of words with Cowboy is, right now, that's a war he can't win. Too much dirt on him right now.
